  "prompt": "How many lokas (like heaven, hell, earth etc.) are there according to Hindu mythology?",
  "response": "In Hindu mythology, there are 14 lokas or realms of existence. These are divided into 7 higher lokas (the heavenly realms) and 7 lower lokas (the netherworlds). Here is a list of the 14 lokas:\n\n**Higher Lokas (Urdhva Lokas):**\n1. Satya Loka (Brahma Loka) - The realm of truth and the abode of Brahma.\n2. Tapo Loka - The realm of austerity and penance.\n3. Jana Loka - The realm of purity and the abode of the sons of Brahma.\n4. Mahar Loka - The realm of great saints and sages.\n5. Svar Loka (Swarga Loka) - The realm of heaven and the abode of the gods.\n6. Bhuvar Loka - The realm of the atmosphere and the abode of the celestial beings.\n7. Bhur Loka (Prithvi Loka) - The realm of earth and the abode of humans.\n\n**Lower Lokas (Adho Lokas):**\n1. Atala Loka - The first of the netherworlds.\n2. Vitala Loka - The second netherworld.\n3. Sutala Loka - The third netherworld and the abode of the demon king Bali.\n4. Talatala Loka - The fourth netherworld.\n5. Mahatala Loka - The fifth netherworld and the abode of the Danavas.\n6. Rasatala Loka - The sixth netherworld and the abode of the Nagas.\n7. Patala Loka - The seventh and lowest netherworld and the abode of the serpent king Vasuki.\n\nThese lokas represent different levels of existence and consciousness within the Hindu cosmological framework.",
